com.yworks.yfiles.graph.portlocationmodels

Interface IPortLocationModelParameter

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ICloneable

    public interface IPortLocationModelParameter
extends ICloneable
    Defines a state that can be used to determine the location of a port with a IPortLocationModel.

    Typically, implementations of this interface are created by factory methods of the corresponding Model.

    This interface extends the ICloneable interface. This allows clients to obtain a persistent copy of the current state of this parameter. Immutable parameter implementations may return themselves.

    See Also:
    IPortLocationModel, IPort

      • supports

        boolean supports(IPortOwner owner)
        Determines whether this parameter can be used for ports at the given owner.

        A parameter must not necessarily support all types of ports. This method returns whether it supports ports at the given owner.

        Parameters:
        owner - The port owner to test.
        Returns:
        true if this instance can be used for ports of the given port owner, false otherwise.
